# Props Rows Fix

The TD columns appeared, but the rows disappeared because the template was too strict about field names.

This update fixes `templates/props.html` so it supports:

- `p.position` or `p.pos`
- `p.market` or `p.prop`
- `p.projection`, `p.bushmaster_proj`, or `p.proj`
- `p.confidence` or `p.confidence_stars`

It also adds:

```text
/props-debug
```

Use that page if rows still do not show. It prints the raw `result.props` data so we can see the actual keys.

## Test

```bash
python app.py
```

Open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:5000/player-props
http://127.0.0.1:5000/props-debug
```
